Pablo Zabaleta proved he's made of stern stuff after playing on in Manchester City's 2-2 draw at home to Burnley, despite suffering a gruesome-looking injury.

The full back took a nasty blow to the face after an accidental clash of heads with team-mate Eliaquim Mangala - as the duo challenged for an aerial ball in the first half.

Images, not for the faint-hearted, show the City medical team applying three stitches to the Argentine full-back, who was cut above his left eye.

