The 29-year-old played the remainder of the game with a bandage wrapped around his head.

Despite his injury, Zabaleta won't be the only City player with a sore head after they threw away the chance to close the gap to one point on league leaders Chelsea.

The hosts took a two-goal lead at the Etihad Stadium courtesy of David Silva and Fernandinho before George Boyd and Ashley Barnes replied for the Clarets after the interval.

City boss Manuel Pellegrini accused his players of complacency after the match and will be demanding his side produce a better display when they host Sunderland on New Years Day.

